header.gameNote: OUTRIGGER RAINBOW CLASSIC AT HONOLULU HI

article.headline: Wyoming 84, San Francisco 81 (OT)
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Brad Jones scored seven of his 26 points in overtime to lead Wyoming to an 84-81 win over San Francisco in a consolation game of the Rainbow Classic on Friday. San Francisco took an 81-80 lead when Alan Wiggins Jr. made a 15-foot jumper with 1:04 left, but Jones scored the final four points to win it for the Cowboys (9-3). San Francisco (4-9) had a chance to retake the lead after Jones made two free throws with 47 seconds left, but Armondo Surratt missed an open layup under the basket. Jones made an 18-footer on Wyoming's next possession. James Spencer and Brandon Ewing added 13 points each for Wyoming. San Francisco was led by Antonio Kellogg's 22-point, 10-rebound performance and Wiggins added 21 points with 11 rebounds. The Cowboys play in Saturday's fifth-place game against Charlotte. San Francisco meets Valparaiso in the seventh-place game.
